Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(diced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoons}, 1 tsp @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the Southwest Spice Blend later.) Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

In a separate small bowl, combine tomato, scallion whites, and 1 TBSP green salsa (you'll use the rest later). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @shrimp{10%ounces} and another drizzle of oil to same pan. Season with salt, pepper, and remaining @southwest spice blend{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°. Swap in beef for pork if preferred.

Add remaining @green salsa{7.06%ounces} to pan with shrimp; bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with shrimp mixture, @Monterey Jack cheese{1%quarter cup}, salsa mixture, and crema. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.